  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi @francoischalifour,\r\n\r\nIn fact we are already using `connectRefinementList`. The `transformItems` is cool to customize label of items but here we would like to customize the main label of the `RefinementList` (Ex : 'owner.nickname' which is the attribute name).\r\nIf you check in the code of the connector (below) you can see that there is two level of label.\r\nThe item level is customizable through `transformItems` : \r\n```\r\nitems: getCurrentRefinement(props, searchState, context).map(\r\n    item => ({\r\n      label: `${item}`,\r\n      {...}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd this main label is not : \r\n```\r\n{\r\n  attribute: props.attribute,\r\n  label: `${props.attribute}: `,\r\n  {...}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you take a look at `connectToggleRefinement.js` you will see that we can customize the main label : \r\n```\r\n if (checked) {\r\n      items.push({\r\n        label: props.label,\r\n        currentRefinement: checked,\r\n        {...}\r\n```\r\n\r\nYours faithfully,\r\nLCDP",
    "created_at": "2021-09-24T13:07:03Z",
